n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>brew install git</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Install Oh My Zsh</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>sh -c \"$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh/master/tools/install.sh)\"</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Install PowerLevel10K Theme for Oh My Zsh</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Clone the PowerLevel10K repo</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>git clone https://github.com/romkatv/powerlevel10k.git $ZSH_CUSTOM/themes/powerlevel10k</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After install, open the \"~/.zshrc\" file with your editor and change the value of \"ZSH_THEME\", following below</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>ZSH_THEME=\"powerlevel10k/powerlevel10k\"</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And run the command below to apply the changes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>source ~/.zshrc</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Configure PowerLevel10K</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Restart iTerm2. You should now be seeing the PowerLevel10K configuration process. If you don\'t, run the following:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>p10k configure</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Follow the instructions for the PowerLevel10K configuration to make your terminal look as desired.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Install ZSH Plugins</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Install zsh-autosuggestions:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>git clone https://github.com/zsh-users/zsh-autosuggestions ${ZSH_CUSTOM:-~/.oh-my-zsh/custom}/plugins/zsh-autosuggestions</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Install zsh-syntax-highlighting:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>git clone https://github.com/zsh-users/zsh-syntax-highlighting.git ${ZSH_CUSTOM:-~/.oh-my-zsh/custom}/plugins/zsh-syntax-highlighting</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Open the \"~/.zshrc\" file in your desired editor and modify the plugins line to what you see below.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>plugins=(git zsh-autosuggestions zsh-syntax-highlighting web-search)</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Load these new plugins by running:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>source ~/.zshrc</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->','','','inherit','closed','closed','','137-revision-v1','','','2023-04-07 19:21:13','2023-04-07 19:21:13','',137,'http://deviofuzz.local/?p=138',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (139,1,'2023-04-07 19:22:08','2023-04-07 19:22:08','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Last updated on&nbsp;Mar 2, 2023</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.deviofuzz.com/content/images/size/w960/2023/03/portainer.png\" alt=\"Portainer.io Instalation and run\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Portainer is a very good container management system. Let\'s install it and take a look at it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>First, you need to create a free account (restrict with 5 nodes) that is enough to have in your home servers for your own usage.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Go to the webpage and create an account and you get an email with the key and instructions on how to install it. I will do it here step by step.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2. Open these ports to be available for Portainer application.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:prismatic/blocks {\"language\":\"bash\"} -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-prismatic-blocks\"><code class=\"language-bash\">>: sudo ufw allow 8000\n>: sudo ufw allow 9443/tcp</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:prismatic/blocks -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3. Download and install the Portainer Server container</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code {\"lineNumbers\":true} -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code lang=\"bash\" class=\"language-bash line-numbers\">&gt;: docker run -d -p 8000:8000 -p 9443:9443 --name=portainer --restart=always \\\n    -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \\\n    -v portainer_data:/data \\\n    portainer/portainer-ee:latest</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>4. Check if the Portainer Server is running.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code {\"lineNumbers\":true} -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code lang=\"bash\" class=\"language-bash line-numbers\">&gt;: docker ps</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>5. Loggin in</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://localhost:9443\">https://localhost:9443</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>6. Create a new user admin and insert the key you got from email.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.deviofuzz.com/content/images/2023/03/image.png\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.deviofuzz.com/content/images/2023/03/image-1.png\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>7. Now it\'s just follow the wizard to add Environments. I think you can take it from here by yourself. Otherwise go to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://install.portainer.io/set-up-portainer?ref=deviofuzz.com\">https://install.portainer.io/set-up-portainer</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Portainer.io Instalation and run','','publish','open','open','','portainer-io-instalation-and-run','','','2023-04-08 23:47:47','2023-04-08 23:47:47','',0,'http://deviofuzz.local/?p=139',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (140,1,'2023-04-07 19:22:08','2023-04-07 19:22:08','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Last updated on&nbsp;Mar 2, 2023</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.deviofuzz.com/content/images/size/w960/2023/03/portainer.png\" alt=\"Portainer.io Instalation and run\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Portainer is a very good container management system. Let\'s install it and take a look at it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>First, you need to create a free account (restrict with 5 nodes) that is enough to have in your home servers for your own usage.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Go to the webpage and create an account and you get an email with the key and instructions on how to install it. I will do it here step by step.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2. Open these ports to be available for Portainer application.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&gt;: sudo ufw allow 8000\n&gt;: sudo ufw allow 9443/tcp\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3. Download and install the Portainer Server container</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&gt;: docker run -d -p 8000:8000 -p 9443:9443 --name=portainer --restart=always \\\n    -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \\\n    -v portainer_data:/data \\\n    portainer/portainer-ee:latest</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>4. Check if the Portainer Server is running.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&gt;: docker ps</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>5. Loggin in</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://localhost:9443\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://localhost:9443\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>6. Create a new user admin and insert the key you got from email.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.deviofuzz.com/content/images/2023/03/image.png\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://www.deviofuzz.com/content/images/2023/03/image-1.png\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>7. Now it\'s just follow the wizard to add Environments. I think you can take it from here by yourself. Otherwise go to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://install.portainer.io/set-up-portainer?ref=deviofuzz.com\">https://install.portainer.io/set-up-portainer</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Portainer.io Instalation and run','','inherit','closed','closed','','139-revision-v1','','','2023-04-07 19:22:08','2023-04-07 19:22:08','',139,'http://deviofuzz.local/?p=140',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (141,1,'2023-04-07 19:22:34','2023-04-07 19:22:34','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Last updated on&nbsp;Feb 26, 2023</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"linkDestination\":\"custom\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1524685794168-52985e79c1f8?crop=entropy&amp;cs=tinysrgb&amp;fit=max&amp;fm=jpg&amp;ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8c2VhcmNofDR8fE1pbmVjcmFmdHxlbnwwfHx8fDE2NzczNjU0Mzk&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;q=80&amp;w=960\" alt=\"Making your own Minecraft server using Docker\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Photo by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@nina_eyes?utm_source=ghost&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=api-credit\">Nina Rivas</a>&nbsp;/&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unsplash.com/?utm_source=ghost&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=api-credit\">Unsplash</a></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Assuming that Docker is working fine in your Linux, create a bash script to easily startup the server, include the command below.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>ubuntu@instance:~$ sudo touch run_minecraft_server\nubuntu@instance:~$ sudo chmod 777 run_minecraft_server</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>#/bin/bash\nsudo docker run -e EULA=TRUE -d -it --name=minecraft-server-dock \\\n  -v ~/bedrock-server:/data \\\n  -e SERVER_NAME=\"My Minecraft Server\" \\\n  -e GAMEMODE=survival \\\n  -e DIFFICULTY=normal \\\n  -e OPS=myusername \\\n  -p 19132:19132/udp \\\n  itzg/minecraft-bedrock-server</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And run the script.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>ubuntu@instance:~$ sudo ./run_minecraft_server</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Obs: If your firewall is enabled, you have to allow the port 19132/udp like below</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>ubuntu@instance:~$ sudo ufw allow 19132/udp\nubuntu@instance:~$ sudo ufw reload</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Interacting with the server</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"http://wiki.vg/RCON?ref=deviofuzz.com\">RCON</a>&nbsp;is enabled by default, so you can&nbsp;<code>exec</code>&nbsp;into the container to access the Minecraft server console:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>#confident_bhaskara is your docker container name \nubuntu@instance:~$ sudo docker exec -i confident_bhaskara rcon-cli</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Note: The&nbsp;<code>-i</code>&nbsp;is required for interactive use of rcon-cli.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To run a simple, one-shot command, such as stopping a Minecraft server, pass the command as arguments to&nbsp;<code>rcon-cli</code>, such as:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>ubuntu@instance:~$ docker exec confident_bhaskara rcon-cli stop\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>The&nbsp;<code>-i</code>&nbsp;is not needed in this case.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If rcon is disabled you can send commands by passing them as arguments to the packaged&nbsp;<code>mc-send-to-console</code>&nbsp;script. For example, a player can be op\'ed in the container&nbsp;<em>confident_bhaskara</em>&nbsp;with:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>ubuntu@instance:~$ docker exec mc mc-send-to-console op player</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In order to attach and interact with the Minecraft server, add&nbsp;<code>-it</code>&nbsp;when starting the container, such as</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>ubuntu@instance:~$ docker run -d -it -p 25565:25565 --name mc itzg/minecraft-server\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With that you can attach and interact at any time using</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>ubuntu@instance:~$ docker attach mc\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>and then Control-p Control-q to&nbsp;<strong>detach</strong>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For remote access, configure your Docker daemon to use a&nbsp;<code>tcp</code>&nbsp;socket (such as&nbsp;<code>-H tcp://0.0.0.0:2375</code>) and attach from another machine:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>ubuntu@instance:~$ docker -H $HOST:2375 attach mc\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Unless you\'re on a home/private LAN, you should&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.docker.com/articles/https/?ref=deviofuzz.com\">enable TLS access</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Making your own Minecraft server using Docker','','publish','open','open','','making-your-own-minecraft-server-using-docker','','','2023-04-08 23:41:42','2023-04-08 23:41:42','',0,'http://deviofuzz.local/?p=141',0,'post','',0);
