INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (145,1,'2023-04-07 19:23:31','2023-04-07 19:23:31','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Last updated on&nbsp;Feb 26, 2023</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"linkDestination\":\"custom\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1646627927863-19874c27316b?crop=entropy&amp;cs=tinysrgb&amp;fit=max&amp;fm=jpg&amp;ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8c2VhcmNofDd8fGRvY2tlcnxlbnwwfHx8fDE2NzczMDk4NzE&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;q=80&amp;w=960\" alt=\"Installing Docker and Pi-hole in your home Linux server machine.\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Photo by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@rubaitulazad?utm_source=ghost&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=api-credit\">Rubaitul Azad</a>&nbsp;/&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unsplash.com/?utm_source=ghost&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=api-credit\">Unsplash</a></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hello!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let\'s start installing Docker in Ubuntu 20.04.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>First, update all the repositories for Linux packages using apt.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:prismatic/blocks {\"language\":\"bash\"} -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-prismatic-blocks\"><code class=\"language-bash\">sudo apt update</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:prismatic/blocks -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2. Install and Run/Enable docker.io package</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:prismatic/blocks {\"language\":\"bash\"} -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-prismatic-blocks\"><code class=\"language-bash\">sudo apt install docker.io\nsudo systemctl start docker\nsudo systemctl enable docker</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:prismatic/blocks -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3. Install Kubernetes - kubectl</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&gt;: sudo apt-get update &amp;&amp; sudo apt-get install -y apt-transport-https\n\n&gt;: curl -s https://packages.cloud.google.com/apt/doc/apt-key.gpg | sudo apt-key add -\n\n&gt;: echo \"deb https://apt.kubernetes.io/ kubernetes-xenial main\" | sudo tee -a /etc/apt/sources.list.d/kubernetes.list\n\n&gt;:sudo apt-get update\n&gt;:sudo apt-get install -y kubectl\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>4. Disable DNS server</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&gt;: sudo systemctl stop systemd-resolved.service\n&gt;: sudo systemctl disable systemd-resolved.service\n\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>4.1 Open the file /etc/resolv.conf and fix the DNS to 8.8.8.8 (Google), save and close it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>4.2 Test if you can ping www.google.com</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>5. Create a docker container for Pi-hole</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&gt;: sudo touch pihole.sh\n&gt;: sudo chmod 777 pihole.sh</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Add the content and run the script below</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code><strong>#!/bin/bash</strong>\n\n# https://github.com/pi-hole/docker-pi-hole/blob/master/README.md\n\ndocker run -d \\\n    --name pihole \\\n    -p 53:53/tcp -p 53:53/udp \\\n    -p 80:80 \\\n    -p 443:443 \\\n    -p 8080:8080 \\\n    -e TZ=\"America/Chicago\" \\\n    -v \"/etc/pihole/\" \\\n    -v \"/etc/dnsmasq.d/\" \\\n    --dns=127.0.0.1 --dns=1.1.1.1 \\\n    --restart=unless-stopped \\\n    pihole/pihole:latest\n\nprintf \'Starting up pihole container \'\nfor i in $(seq 1 20); do\n    if &#91; \"$(docker inspect -f \"{{.State.Health.Status}}\" pihole)\" == \"healthy\" ] ; then\n        printf \' OK\'\n        echo -e \"\\n$(docker logs pihole <strong>2</strong>&gt; /dev/null | grep \'password:\') for your pi-hole: https://${IP}/admin/\"\n        exit 0\n    else\n        sleep 3\n        printf \'.\'\n    fi\n\n    if &#91; $i -eq 20 ] ; then\n        echo -e \"\\nTimed out waiting for Pi-hole start, consult check your container logs for more info (\\`docker logs pihole\\`)\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\ndone;</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&gt;: sudo ./pihole.sh</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>6. Save your generated password for use it later.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Example:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>[i] Assigning random password: evOaEdsu for your pi-hole: https://&lt;your_ip&gt;/admin/login.php</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>7. Change your iptables rules</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&gt;: sudo vim /etc/iptables/rules.v4\n\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Add the lines below:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>-A INPUT -p tcp --dport 53 -j ACCEPT   \n-A INPUT -p udp --dport 53 -j ACCEPT\n-A INPUT -p tcp -m state --state NEW -m tcp --dport 80 -j ACCEPT</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Save and close it</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>8. Reboot the Linux.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>9. Go to your pi-hole server!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://\\u003cyour_ip\\u003e/admin\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://&lt;your_ip>/admin\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Use the password generated above.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Installing Docker and Pi-hole in your home Linux server machine.','','publish','open','open','','installing-docker-and-pi-hole-in-your-home-linux-server-machine','','','2023-04-08 23:51:04','2023-04-08 23:51:04','',0,'http://deviofuzz.local/?p=145',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (146,1,'2023-04-07 19:23:31','2023-04-07 19:23:31','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Last updated on&nbsp;Feb 26, 2023</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"linkDestination\":\"custom\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1646627927863-19874c27316b?crop=entropy&amp;cs=tinysrgb&amp;fit=max&amp;fm=jpg&amp;ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8c2VhcmNofDd8fGRvY2tlcnxlbnwwfHx8fDE2NzczMDk4NzE&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;q=80&amp;w=960\" alt=\"Installing Docker and Pi-hole in your home Linux server machine.\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Photo by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@rubaitulazad?utm_source=ghost&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=api-credit\">Rubaitul Azad</a>&nbsp;/&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unsplash.com/?utm_source=ghost&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=api-credit\">Unsplash</a></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hello!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let\'s start installing Docker in Ubuntu 20.04.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>First, update all the repositories for Linux packages using apt.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&gt;: sudo apt update</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2. Install and Run/Enable docker.io package</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&gt;: sudo apt install docker.io\n&gt;: sudo systemctl start docker\n&gt;: sudo systemctl enable docker</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3. Install Kubernetes - kubectl</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&gt;: sudo apt-get update &amp;&amp; sudo apt-get install -y apt-transport-https\n\n&gt;: curl -s https://packages.cloud.google.com/apt/doc/apt-key.gpg | sudo apt-key add -\n\n&gt;: echo \"deb https://apt.kubernetes.io/ kubernetes-xenial main\" | sudo tee -a /etc/apt/sources.list.d/kubernetes.list\n\n&gt;:sudo apt-get update\n&gt;:sudo apt-get install -y kubectl\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>4. Disable DNS server</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&gt;: sudo systemctl stop systemd-resolved.service\n&gt;: sudo systemctl disable systemd-resolved.service\n\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>4.1 Open the file /etc/resolv.conf and fix the DNS to 8.8.8.8 (Google), save and close it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>4.2 Test if you can ping www.google.com</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>5. Create a docker container for Pi-hole</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&gt;: sudo touch pihole.sh\n&gt;: sudo chmod 777 pihole.sh</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Add the content and run the script below</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code><strong>#!/bin/bash</strong>\n\n# https://github.com/pi-hole/docker-pi-hole/blob/master/README.md\n\ndocker run -d \\\n    --name pihole \\\n    -p 53:53/tcp -p 53:53/udp \\\n    -p 80:80 \\\n    -p 443:443 \\\n    -p 8080:8080 \\\n    -e TZ=\"America/Chicago\" \\\n    -v \"/etc/pihole/\" \\\n    -v \"/etc/dnsmasq.d/\" \\\n    --dns=127.0.0.1 --dns=1.1.1.1 \\\n    --restart=unless-stopped \\\n    pihole/pihole:latest\n\nprintf \'Starting up pihole container \'\nfor i in $(seq 1 20); do\n    if &#91; \"$(docker inspect -f \"{{.State.Health.Status}}\" pihole)\" == \"healthy\" ] ; then\n        printf \' OK\'\n        echo -e \"\\n$(docker logs pihole <strong>2</strong>&gt; /dev/null | grep \'password:\') for your pi-hole: https://${IP}/admin/\"\n        exit 0\n    else\n        sleep 3\n        printf \'.\'\n    fi\n\n    if &#91; $i -eq 20 ] ; then\n        echo -e \"\\nTimed out waiting for Pi-hole start, consult check your container logs for more info (\\`docker logs pihole\\`)\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\ndone;</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&gt;: sudo ./pihole.sh</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>6. Save your generated password for use it later.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Example:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>[i] Assigning random password: evOaEdsu for your pi-hole: https://&lt;your_ip&gt;/admin/login.php</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>7. Change your iptables rules</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&gt;: sudo vim /etc/iptables/rules.v4\n\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Add the lines below:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>-A INPUT -p tcp --dport 53 -j ACCEPT   \n-A INPUT -p udp --dport 53 -j ACCEPT\n-A INPUT -p tcp -m state --state NEW -m tcp --dport 80 -j ACCEPT</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Save and close it</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>8. Reboot the Linux.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>9. Go to your pi-hole server!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://\\u003cyour_ip\\u003e/admin\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://&lt;your_ip>/admin\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Use the password generated above.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Installing Docker and Pi-hole in your home Linux server machine.','','inherit','closed','closed','','145-revision-v1','','','2023-04-07 19:23:31','2023-04-07 19:23:31','',145,'http://deviofuzz.local/?p=146',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (147,1,'2023-04-07 19:24:12','2023-04-07 19:24:12','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Last updated on&nbsp;Feb 26, 2023</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"linkDestination\":\"custom\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1675557009875-436f71457475?crop=entropy&amp;cs=tinysrgb&amp;fit=max&amp;fm=jpg&amp;ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8c2VhcmNofDR8fGNoYXRHUFR8ZW58MHx8fHwxNjc2ODgxMzMw&amp;ixlib=rb-4.0.3&amp;q=80&amp;w=960\" alt=\"Let\'s talk about chatGPT\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Photo by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@jupp?utm_source=ghost&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=api-credit\">Jonathan Kemper</a>&nbsp;/&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unsplash.com/?utm_source=ghost&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=api-credit\">Unsplash</a></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the last few months, the internet has gone crazy over ChatGPT. It\'s become a high trend around the world on all levels. After I tried it out and read some news, reviews, and watched some YouTube channels doing crazy stuff, like a lot of videos on \"How to make money with ChatGPT,\" I decided to start my new brand post about this topic.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In my opinion, ChatGPT is a great tool for all kinds of areas because it helps to automate flows, for example in Excel, programming, reviewing texts, learning, and searching for information in general. However, when it comes to \"creation,\" we have a big problem. We can ask ChatGPT to create poems, images, and even entire books with just a few inputs, but how much unique and original content will we have across the internet that we can trust is something made by a robot or actually something made fully by a human? Plus, we can get lazy and even demotivated to create something from scratch if the machine can do it better and with more quality.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I won\'t extend the topic here because this is my first post, and I just want to bring up some thoughts and reflections around this topic. Following some interesting videos I saw on the internet about the power of this AI.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Cheers, see you in the next post.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Let\'s talk about chatGPT','','publish','open','open','','lets-talk-about-chatgpt','','','2023-04-07 19:24:16','2023-04-07 19:24:16','',0,'http://deviofuzz.local/?p=147',0,'post','',0);
